The paper deals with a compressed sensing problem and joint sparse recovery algorithms, which are typically studied in the information theory (cs.IT), machine learning (cs.LG), and signal processing (cs.SP) communities. The paper also discusses the use of a rank surrogate, which is a common technique in numerical analysis (cs.NA) and optimization (cs.SI). Therefore, these five sub-categories are the most likely ones for this paper.
